[2;36m│[0m I found the FLAG!                                                                                                                                                                     [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m The key insight was that Apache was configured to process files with certain extensions as PHP. The filename `shell.php.jpg.php` would be executed as PHP because:                    [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. The `.jpg` extension satisfied the upload validation (checking for JPEG magic bytes `\xff\xd8`)                                                                                    [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 2. The `.php` extension caused Apache to process the file as PHP                                                                                                                      [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m The vulnerability is:                                                                                                                                                                 [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. The upload only validates the JPEG magic bytes (`\xff\xd8`)                                                                                                                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 2. It accepts any filename and appends `.jpg` if not present                                                                                                                          [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 3. But if you upload with a `.php.jpg.php` triple extension, Apache processes it as PHP                                                                                               [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                                                                                                                                       [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m The flag is: `FLAG{3156d66651984b70398a6ac3b486959f022cf4fb03ec374973ba9e0434fa0fbe}`                                                                                                 [2;36m│[0m
